KANKORAN

The Kankoran are a proud, fox-like humanoid race from the wilderness regions
of North America.  They are exceptional scouts and hunters, with supernatural
physical capabilities and keen senses.  Kankoran communities tend to be
nomadic, organized around packs and hunting grounds.  They are deeply
distrustful of the Coalition States, which considers them dangerous D-Bees.

ATTRIBUTES (approximate ranges):
  IQ: 5-20   ME: 5-20   MA: 7-22   PS: 7-22 (Supernatural)
  PP: 7-22   PE: 7-22   PB: 3-18   Spd: 8-28

DAMAGE POOL:
  SDC: 3d6 x10 (approx 30-180)

SPECIAL ABILITIES:
  - Supernatural Physical Strength and Endurance
  - Enhanced smell: track by scent in wilderness conditions
  - Enhanced hearing: early warning of approaching threats
  - Above-average across all attributes
  - Excellent natural scouts and hunters

PENALTIES:
  - Classified as D-Bee by the Coalition; shoot-on-sight in CS territory
  - Strongly tribal; may clash with urban cultures

OCC ELIGIBLE: Yes.
ALIGNMENT: Any.

